Spialia mafa, the Mafa grizzled skipper or Mafa sandman, is a butterfly of the family Hesperiidae. It is found in south-western Africa, in KwaZulu-Natal, Botswana, Zimbabwe and from the Cape in South Africa to Sudan and southern Arabia.
These skippers are dark brown with white spots and both sides of the wings.Wingspan is from 22â€“26 mm.Flight period is year-round but peaks from September to April.The larvae feed on Hermannia, Pavonia and Hibiscus species (including Hibiscus aethiopicus).